	<div class="textBoxClass">
	<h1>Careers at Naked Kitchens</h1>
	<p>Naked Kitchens is a rapidly growing company that is always looking out for talented fresh-thinkers to join our friendly team. If you would like to apply for a job, please send your CV & covering letter to <a href="mailto:careers@nakedkitchens.com">careers@nakedkitchens.com</a></p>
    <p>Please ensure that you have read the job description below, and meet the criteria we require before applying.</p>
</div>


<div class="textBoxLeftClass">
    <h2>TRAINEE KITCHEN DESIGNER </h2>
    <div style="text-align:justify; padding:12px; margin-top:8px; margin-bottom:40px; border-top:6px solid #D3D3D3; border-left:1px solid #D3D3D3; border-right:1px solid #D3D3D3; border-bottom:1px solid #D3D3D3;">
        <p><p>NAKED Kitchens is a rapidly growing company that is always looking out for talented fresh thinkers to join our friendly team. <br />Please ensure that you have read the job description below, and meet the criteria we require before applying.</p>
<p><strong>You need to:</strong></p>
<p>- Be dynamic, eager to learn and work as part of an energetic and outgoing team<br />- Have excellent numerical and writing skills, and be able to advise customers in a professional yet friendly manner<br />- Have an eye for detail, a taste for interior design and a desire to create kitchens and furniture to the finest level<br />- Have a willingness to learn, and a flair for problem solving and precision and an ability to understand construction methods and the mathematical processes involved in kitchen design<br />- Have previous experience using CAD software or similar programmes<br /><br /></p>
<p><strong>Your role at NAKED Kitchens will involve:</strong><br />- Guiding each customer through their kitchen project via telephone, email and in person<br />- Create customer's kitchen plans using our CAD software (Training will be provided)<br />- Working alongside our designers to ensure a high quality service and a flawless kitchen design for every customer<br />- Liaising with our workshop team to bring kitchens into production and monitor to completion</p>
<p><strong>The position is full time, and working hours are Monday to Friday 9am until 5.30pm. Due to our location in rural North Norfolk a full driving licence is essential.</strong></p></p>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="textBoxLeftClass">
    <h2>EXPERIENCED KITCHEN DESIGNER</h2>
    <div style="text-align:justify; padding:12px; margin-top:8px; margin-bottom:40px; border-top:6px solid #D3D3D3; border-left:1px solid #D3D3D3; border-right:1px solid #D3D3D3; border-bottom:1px solid #D3D3D3;">
        <p><p>NAKED Kitchens is a rapidly growing company that is always looking out for talented fresh thinkers to join our friendly team. <br /><br /></p>
<p><strong>You need to:</strong></p>
<p>- Be dynamic, eager to learn and work as part of an energetic and outgoing team<br />- Have excellent numerical and writing skills, and be able to advise customers in a professional yet friendly manner<br />- Have an eye for detail, a taste for interior design and a desire to create kitchens and furniture to the finest level<br />- Have a willingness to learn, and a flair for problem solving and precision and the ability to understand construction methods and the mathematical processes involved in design <br />- Have experience using CAD software or similar programmes<br />- Have a focus on creative application</p>
<p><strong>Your role at NAKED Kitchens will involve:</strong><br />- Guiding each customer through their kitchen project via telephone, email and in person<br />- Create customer's kitchen plans using our CAD software <br />- Working alongside our designers to ensure a high quality service and a flawless kitchen design for every customer<br />- Liaising with our workshop team to bring kitchens into production and monitor to completion</p>
<p><strong>The position is full time, and working hours are Monday to Friday 9am until 5.30pm. Due to our location in rural North Norfolk a full driving licence is essential.</strong></p></p>
    </div>
</div>


<div class="textBoxLeftClass">
    <h2>GRADUATE TRAINEE PRODUCT MANAGER </h2>
    <div style="text-align:justify; padding:12px; margin-top:8px; margin-bottom:40px; border-top:6px solid #D3D3D3; border-left:1px solid #D3D3D3; border-right:1px solid #D3D3D3; border-bottom:1px solid #D3D3D3;">
        <p><p>Manufacturer of high quality, beautiful bespoke kitchens; Naked Kitchens is looking for a talented fresh thinker to join our fast-growing, friendly team. </p>
<p><strong>The Position:</strong><br />We are looking for a Graduate Trainee Product Manager to work in our friendly office team.</p>
<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong><br />Your role at Naked Kitchens will involve:</p>
<p>- Developing a new product and brand under the Naked Kitchens umbrella.<br />- Marketing and Business Development.<br />- Preparing working documentation to aid manufacture within our workshop.<br />- Liasing with our workshop team to bring orders into production and monitor completion.<br />- Strategic thinking and decision making. </p>
<p><strong>The Person:</strong><br />You will:</p>
<p>- Have excellent communication skills; both written and spoken.<br />- Possess good analytical and mathematical skills and be a clear thinker.<br />- Have strong strategic thinking and be able to work on your own initiative.<br />- Have high levels of organisation, creativity and flair.<br />- Have the ability to prioritize your workload to meet deadlines. <br />- Work well under pressure and in a fast paced environment.<br />- Be educated to degree level.</p>
<p>The position is full time, and working hours are Monday to Friday 9am until 5.30pm. Due to our location in rural North Norfolk a full driving licence is essential.</p></p>
    </div>
</div>


